  CurrentLogLevel: 3
  m_statusReadOnly: 
  _toolName: ToDoListDisplayTool
  _toolPriority: 1000
  _descriptionForPrompt: 'Use this tool when the user asks to see, show, open, display,
    hide, or close the full to-do list UI.


    If this call is made from the user''s
    speech, call it as usual. if the user requests a to-do list from a text communication
    source (like Discord), ignore this tool call unless the user explicitly asks
    "Show it on your screen" "or "Show it on the screen" or something similar.


    This
    tool does NOT accept task list contents from the model.

    It reads the current
    to-do list directly from the application''s internal task state and displays
    that state in a large UI view.


    Use this tool only to control visibility
    of the to-do list display.


    Important rules:

    - Do NOT include task
    items in the payload.

    - Do NOT attempt to restate or reconstruct the to-do
    list in the payload.

    - The display always uses the current internal task
    state.

    - If the user asks to show the to-do list, use option "show".

    -
    If the user asks to hide or close the to-do list, use option "hide".

    - If
    the user asks to show the to-do list for a specific time, convert that request
    into durationMinutes as a float in minutes.

    - If the user asks to keep the
    list visible indefinitely, omit durationMinutes.

    - If the user simply asks
    to show the to-do list without specifying a duration, default to durationMinutes
    = 5.


    Examples:

    - 20 minutes -> 20

    - 30 seconds -> 0.5

    -
    1 hour -> 60'
  _jsonPayloadExampleForPrompt: "A valid example payload for showing the to-do list
    for 5 minutes:\n\n{\n  \"option\": \"show\",\n  \"durationMinutes\": 5\n}\n\nA
    valid example payload for showing the to-do list for 30 seconds:\n\n{\n  \"option\":
    \"show\",\n  \"durationMinutes\": 0.5\n}\n\nA valid example payload for showing
    the to-do list indefinitely:\n\n{\n  \"option\": \"show\"\n}\n\nA valid example
    payload for hiding the to-do list:\n\n{\n  \"option\": \"hide\"\n}"
  _toDoListDisplayPrefab: {fileID: 0}
  _toDoListText: {fileID: 0}
  _importantTextColor: {r: 0.6431373, g: 0, b: 0.07445346, a: 1}
  _normalTextColor: {r: 0.02761037, g: 0, b: 0.21698111, a: 1}
  _urgentPrefix: '[URGENT] '
  _highPriorityPrefix: '[IMPORTANT] '
